'''Cultural encoding''' is a process in which a [[website]] or related node is "encoded" with the [[language]], symbols, or representative styles of particular [[culture]] or [[subculture]]. "Encoding" refers to the [[Digital data|digital]] processes that make the representative culture of the site self-evident.

For example, interpunk.com uses punk [[iconography]] including a [[mohawk hairstyle|mohawk]] [[icon]], [[font]]s, and a do it yourself interface for selling music that cleary establishes the [[Punk subculture|punk]] identity of the site.

